Vietnam  aims to limit its trade
deficit to no more than $10 billion next year, the National
Assembly said in a document handed to reporters at a briefing in
Hanoi today.  The trade deficit will be kept at below 10 percent of the
countryâ€™s total exports in 2012, according to the document. The
nation will also aim to keep its  budget deficit  at below 4.5
percent of gross domestic product, and limit public debt to no
more than 60 percent of GDP in 2012.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
